        <div class="commentContent">As an avid gardener both indoors and out I save all plastic lids that I feel are big enough to sit a plant pot on. That can be quite a broad range. I have some succulents that are in 2 inch pots and pots that are several gallons. I find plastic lids make excellent saucers. Unlike clay saucers which can leave moisture deposits on a window sill or your wood coffee table, the plastic alternatives do not. Since plastic lids come in a wide range of colors (clear, white, red, blue, black, etc.) they can blend into the decor quite nicely. You can save money too because when you buy a pot oftentimes the saucer costs extra. :-) </div>
