        <div class="commentContent">A teaching idea I use with my students is saving the water lids and printing a letter of the alphabet on each one with a permanent marker.  When the students practice their spelling words, they use the  letters to spell the words.  You might also want to put vowels on with another color permanent marker so the students can see the make-up of the word.  

Parents can also have students do this at home with their spelling lists.  All children learn differently and this is just one more way where children learn using their hands.  It also teaches them recycling because they will come up with many more uses for the caps than the adults! </div>
