        <div class="commentContent">I use bottle caps to put small amounts of paint in. If a project I am working on just needs a touch up, the lid will take a small amount, saves lots of paint. 

I also am a crazy quilter (those of you who know may not comment!) &amp; take a tin of embroidery work w/me all the time. I put my threads on bobbins from my sewing machine. Once filled with thread, I put the bobbin in the Diet Pepsi cap, perfect! It keeps my threads from getting tangled &amp; makes the tin neat so I can find colors when I need them.</div>
    </div>
