        <div class="commentContent">Having grown up in Europe I know that almost everything can be recycled. Last time I was home my brother told me that Germany recycles 99% of their garbage. Garbage is a big business over there. He doesn&#039;t understand why it isn&#039;t here. They actually pay people to go through your garbage a few times a year and if you aren&#039;t recycling it correctly you get fined. Everything there gets picked up at your house except glass and clothing. There are huge bubbles in town that you can put these items in for recycling. The clothing goes to third world countries (used to go to the eastern block countries) for them to reuse and they were glad to get it.

It is frustrating here that we don&#039;t recycle more. I had my whole street recycling a few years ago. We used to have a recycling place at the end of our street that was there once a week but now that they took it away nobody recycles anymore except me.</div>
