    <div class="commentWrapper" style="background: url('http://www.recyclebank.com/skin/frontend/enterprise/blank//images/product-line.png') repeat-x scroll center bottom transparent;">
        <div class="commentDetails">
            <h4 class="username">
                Diana Garcia            </h4>
            <div class="commentDate">
                May 4, 2011            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="commentContent">what I&#039;ve been doing with the caps, specially the larger ones, I use these as a protection to avoid the rust to get on the tile floor. this happens if you have platers which legs are made of metal, and because water is involved in the process of watering your plants, or if you live in FL like I do, the humidity always rusts these &quot;feet&quot;.  So I am placing one cap in between the floor and the planter or pot stand leg and works perfectly.  The larger cap as the one that comes with the orange juice plastic bottles is the ideal one.
Try it!</div>
    </div>
