        <div class="commentContent">I sort all our garbage and take recyling and trash directly to our closest county recycling location. However, they only accept #s 1 &amp; 2, so I throw the lids away. However, I create very little waste to begin with and every couple of months, I encourage the county employee at the recycling center to remember that we need to step up what we are able to recycle there. Right now, they do not accept styrofoam for example, but I can take it to Publix. I have not used a new Subway cup in months, as I bring in all the ones I never threw out and they give me two free cookies for bringing my own cup. Why through them out when you can reuse them? Going to work on the cap issue now with our county. Thanks for all you do. I love our earth and want to do all I can to preserve it and it&#039;s health.</div>
